title: Fazal Hakeem wins PK-6 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Fazal Hakeem Khan has won the election for Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly constituency PK-6 Swat-IV by securing 25,330 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Iftikhar Ahmed of Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf-Parliamentarian, who bagged 19,422 votes.
The overall votersâ€™ turnout remained 40.35 percent.
